7. Error handling and retries

Error classes

Use normalized classes:
	•	RetryableApiError
	•	RateLimitedError
	•	AuthenticationError
	•	ValidationError
	•	InsufficientFundsError
	•	StaleDataError
	•	NonRetryableApiError

Retry policy

Hyperliquid
	•	respect documented rate limits and WebSocket connection limits
	•	light reads: exponential backoff, short max wait
	•	trading: max 3 attempts, reconcile before resubmission

Hyperliquid documents weighted REST limits and WebSocket connection/subscription constraints.  ￼

Polymarket
	•	public reads: short exponential retries
	•	trading: retry only on timeout, 429, transient server issues
	•	never blindly resubmit orders without reconciliation

Polymarket distinguishes public reads from authenticated CLOB operations and documents rate-limit behavior in the API docs.  ￼

Non-stop runtime rule

Program must never exit on recoverable errors.
Instead:
	•	log
	•	retry
	•	degrade venue
	•	skip cycle
	•	continue loop

8. MVP strategy policy

MVP should support only one production candidate class:

spot_plus_pm_range_with_backup

Structure:
	•	buy spot on Hyperliquid
	•	buy primary Polymarket range
	•	optionally buy lower backup range
	•	discard if downside is too expensive or not backupeable

This keeps the first version narrow, testable, and aligned with the filtering logic already defined.

